{"questionId":"27766","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>In this question you will investigate series of the form</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mi>q</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>where&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p><strong>and use various methods to find polynomials, in terms of</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi></math>, <strong>for such series.</strong></p>\n<p>When&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, the above series is arithmetic.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the case when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>You will now consider a method that can be generalized for all values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and consider the following family of functions:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>q</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.<br>The second <em><strong>A1</strong></em> is dependent on the first <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>Award a maximum of <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em> if a general term is not considered.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mo>d</mo><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mi>i</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mi>i</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mfenced><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27766","referenceCode":"22N.3.AHL.TZ0.1d.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that f2x=Σi=1ni2xi.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}